cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CY 

The paper proposes a computational model of language comprehension for cognitive agents, which involves multiple information sources including perceptions, domain knowledge, and experiences. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, such as cs.CL (Computation and Language) for its focus on language processing, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) for its use of computational models, cs.LG (Machine Learning) for its incorporation of learning mechanisms, cs.RO (Robotics) for its application to physical worlds, and cs.CY (Computers and Society) for its potential impact on human-computer interactions.
